<p><a name="Cultural_impact" id="Cultural_impact"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=M16_rifle&amp;action=edit&amp;section=31" title="Edit section: Cultural impact">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Cultural impact</span></h2>
<p>The M16 and its variants are ubiquitous in American and many other countries' <a href="/wiki/Film" title="Film">films</a>, <a href="/wiki/Television_program" title="Television program">TV series</a> and <a href="/wiki/Video_game" title="Video game">video games</a>. Among U.S. firearms owners, fully automatic civilian M16 model production was restricted after 1986.</p>
